    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nOn the CI, the Windows 3.9 `carray_iteration` test is occasionally failing with:\n\n```\nOSError: [Errno 28] No space left on device\n```\n\nSee https://github.com/cython/cython/actions/runs/21789518877/job/62866364471 for an example of a failed run.\n\nIt's obvious a fairly large source file.\n\nWhen I compiled it locally on MSVC/Windows the `.pyd` file is ~2.5 MB and the `.obj` file is ~10 MB. So large, but nothing particularly excessive. It's possible that it's creating temporary files elsewhere that I don't know about though.\n\nThere's a small space-saving to be had with `cython: binding=False`. However it's only a few percent so likely not enough. There might be a larger space-saving by moving all the docstrings into a module-level docstrings (at the cost of readability). I haven't actually measured this.",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-16T05:40:19Z",
